# Macro Signal Engine — Hard Constraints

## Competition Rules (NEVER VIOLATE)
- inference.py MUST use OpenAI client only — no anthropic, no transformers, no local models
- Required env vars: API_BASE_URL, MODEL_NAME, HF_TOKEN — never hardcode these
- inference.py runtime MUST be < 20 minutes total across all 3 tasks
- Machine budget: 2 vCPU, 8 GB RAM — no scipy, statsmodels, torch, or heavy libs
- Rewards MUST be floats in [0.0, 1.0] — assert this at every grader return point
- 3 tasks minimum: single_event (easy), regime_shift (medium), causal_chain (hard)
- Graders MUST be deterministic — no random seeds at grader call time

## OpenEnv Spec (NEVER VIOLATE)
- Port MUST be read from os.environ["PORT"], default 7860 for HF Spaces (NOT 8000)
- Dockerfile MUST use non-root user (useradd / USER user) — HF Spaces requirement
- WebSocket (/ws) is PRIMARY transport — HTTP /reset /step are debug-only
- openenv.yaml MUST be present and valid — checked by openenv validate
- All Pydantic models use model_config = {"frozen": True}

## Dependency Direction (NEVER REVERSE)
- models.py has NO local imports
- client.py imports from models.py ONLY
- server/environment.py imports from models.py ONLY
- server/app.py imports from server/environment.py and models.py
- inference.py imports from client.py and models.py
- NOTHING imports from server/ except app.py

## Reward Rules
- All grader functions MUST end with: assert 0.0 <= reward <= 1.0, f"Reward {reward} out of range"
- Step-level partial rewards required — not just terminal rewards
- Penalize no-ops: -0.02 per idle step when signal_events is non-empty (after normalization)
- Transaction cost penalty built into causal_chain grader

## Scenario Bank Rules
- data/scenarios.json is the ONLY source of scenario data — no hardcoded scenarios in env
- price_path MUST have exactly max_steps + 1 entries per asset
- Validate scenarios at server startup — fail fast if malformed
- scenario_id values must be globally unique across all task types

## Code Style
- No print() in server code — use logging
- All async functions in app.py, all sync in environment.py
- Type hints on every function signature
- No bare except: — always catch specific exception types
